lay that shows up on scroll -->\\n<aside id=\"left_context_metadata\" class=\"js_control_bar_recall left_context_metadata\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\\n<div class=\"metadata\">\\n<header>For Amazon, Now Comes the Hard Part - WSJ</header>\\n\\n<div class=\"source\">\\n<div class=\"site_name\">\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/for-amazon-now-comes-the-hard-part-1497827240\">wsj.com</a>\\n</div>\\n\\n<div class=\"site_domain\">\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/for-amazon-now-comes-the-hard-part-1497827240\">WSJ</a>\\n</div>\\n\\n</div>\\n\\n\\n<time class=\"meta_read_time\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\\n0 min\\n</time>\\n\\n</div>\\n\\n</aside>\\n</section>\\n<section id=\"swap_logo_capital\" class=\"js_control_bar_recall swap_logo_capital\">\\n<aside class=\"logo_capital\"></aside>\\n</section>\\n<section id=\"recall_indicator\" class=\"recall_indicator\">\\n<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" class=\"js_control_bar_recall\">\\n<span class=\"ipicon ipicon-ellipsis\"></span>\\n</a>\\n</section>\\n</nav>\\n\\n</div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\"container read_content_container\">\\n<main class=\"main\" aria-label=\"Article\">\\n\\n<div class=\"badge-container read-tag-container js_read_tag_container\"></div>\\n<div id=\"titlebar\" class=\"titlebar\">\\n<h1>For Amazon, Now Comes the Hard Part - WSJ</h1>\\n<span class=\"origin_line\">\\n\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/for-amazon-now-comes-the-hard-part-1497827240\">WSJ</a>\\n\\n&middot;\\n\\nby <span class=\"author\">Julie Jargon, Annie Gasparro and Heather Haddon</span>\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n</span>\\n\\n</div>\\n<div id=\"story\"data-id=\"921020408\" data-words=\"163\" class=\"story\">\\n<div><div><div><div><h2>The e-commerce titan may be the player most likely to persuade Americans to buy fresh food online, but it must first solve the \\xe2\\x80\\x98last mile\\xe2\\x80\\x99 logistics puzzle</h2></div></div></div><article><div><section><div><figure><figcaption>Amazon\\'s $13.7 billion acquisition of Whole Foods Market makes the online retailer a major player in the grocery sector. WSJ\\'s Tanya Rivero outlines three things to know about the deal. Photo: Zuma Press</figcaption></figure></div><p>With  wheeling sharply into the grocery aisle, the business of selling food may never be the same.</p><p>Food retailing was <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/kroger-shares-slide-as-grocer-is-battered-by-price-fight-1497531764?mod=article_inline\">already struggling</a> with low margins and slow sales growth as shoppers shifted buying patterns. New players have swarmed the crowded market, with grocers ranging from giants <span><a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WMT\">Wal-Mart Stores</a></span> Inc. and Kroger Co. to smaller chains fighting to attract consumers, in large part by <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/lower-prices-at-wal-mart-good-for-shoppers-bad-for-grocers-1492689601?mod=article_inline\">slashing prices</a>.</p><p>And the industry has been struggling to figure out how to sell fresh food online.</p><div><figure><picture><img src=\"https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/BN-TX543_GROCER_E_20170618164239.jpg\"></picture></figure><figcaption><span>A Whole Foods Market in Newark, N.J.</span> <span><span>Photo: </span>Richard B. Levine/Zuma Press</span></figcaption></div></section><p>Copyright \\xc2\\xa92024 Dow Jones &amp; Company, Inc. All Rights Reserved. 87990cbe856818d5eddac44c7b1cdeb8</p></div></article></div>\\n</div>\\n<footer id=\"footer\" class=\"footer\">\\n<span class=\"origin_line\">\\n\\n<a class=\"original\" href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/for-amazon-now-comes-the-hard-part-1497827240\">WSJ</a>\\n\\n&middot;\\n\\nby <span class=\"author\">Julie Jargon, Annie Gasparro and Heather Haddon</span>\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n</span>\\n</footer>\\n<!-- ### Parser\\nInstaparser\\n-->\\n</main>\\n</div>\\n<!-- Modals -->\\n<div id=\"modal_backer\" class=\"modal_backer\"></div>\\n\\n\\n<div id=\\'speedTimeRem